{
    "name": "Rat Swarm",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> any<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, pack (2\u20135 swarms), or infestation (6\u201312 swarms)<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Disease (Ex)</b> Filth fever: Swarm\u2014injury; <i>save </i>Fort DC 12; <i>onset </i>1d3 days; <i>frequency </i>1/day; <i>effect </i>1d3 Dex damage and 1d3 Con damage; cure 2 consecutive saves. The save DC is Constitution-based."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "A rat swarm typically consists of a biting, roiling mass of hundreds of disease-ridden rats driven to uncharacteristic heights of aggression by fantastic and overwhelming hunger. In such numbers, they become voracious hunters, capable of killing a full-grown human with hundreds of bites. Rat swarms are often found in the sewers of large human settlements.<br/><br/>Rat swarms surround and attack any warm-blooded prey in their path."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>A squirming, roiling mass of squeaking rats draws closer, teeth flashing and claws scratching everything in its path.</i>",
